    "In both, the Desktop devices were the most widely used (73.2%), because they can run larger and more detailed environments (e.g., Irshad et al. 2021).",
    "In contrast, Standalone (14.6%) and Cardboard (2.4%) HMDs were less used, in view of their limited storage capacity and mobility, (e.g., Adhyaru and Kemp 2022; Varela-Aldás et al. 2019, respectively).",
    "The same was observed when the Explorative experiences were also interactives.",
    "Those sorts of experiences are the most difficult to develop, because they require advanced development and lengthier investment times.",
